headline.main: FOE ON INDIES ISLE; Armada Lands Soldiers in West and Central Sections of Java BATAVIA IS FLANKED 3 Japanese Destroyers and Cruiser Put Out of Action Earlier

lead_paragraph: BATAVIA, Netherlands Indies, Sunday, March 1 -- Japanese invasion forces ran a gantlet of United Nations warships and planes and landed last night and early today in the western and central parts of Java, the last bastion of the United Nations in the Netherlands Indies. Defending American, Netherland and Australian forces engaged the invaders.
